# 8. Agent & Tool Design (Google ADK)

## 8.1 High-level agents

* **Ordering Agent** (frontline): accepts NLU result; resolves candidate med(s); queries inventory; presents user choices; asks clarifying questions (multi-turn).
* **Safety Agent**: enforced by orchestrator tools; checks `rx_required`, blocks or asks for confirmation.
* **Forecast Agent**: runs for chronic meds to compute depletion and generate timeline.
* **Procurement Agent**: placeholder (v2) — prepares procurement payloads (not active in MVP).

## 8.2 Tool Interface (the agent calls these)

* `tool.queryByIndication(indication: string) -> [med_ids]`
* `tool.queryByName(name: string) -> [candidates{id,score}]`
* `tool.getInventory(med_id) -> {stock_quantity}`
* `tool.getRxFlag(med_id) -> {rx_required}`
* `tool.addToCart(med_id, qty) -> cart_state`
* `tool.getHistory(user_id, med_id) -> []` (for forecast)
* `tool.log_trace(trace_obj) -> ack`

Tools are thin wrappers over DB/Chroma and return JSON. Agents never access DB directly.

