# 9. NLU & Model Selection

## 9.1 NLU (small model)

* Purpose: intent classification and entity extraction.
* Candidate models (OpenRouter free tier): `mistral-7b-instruct` / `qwen2.5-7b` / similar.
* Must enforce JSON response format (strict schema) to avoid hallucinations.

## 9.2 Planner / Reasoner (larger model)

* Purpose: planning, multi-step decisions, question generation, confirmation prompts.
* Candidate models (OpenRouter mid/large): `qwen2.5-72b`, `deepseek-r1`, `claude-3-sonnet` if available.
* Keep prompt templates short and deterministic; prefer few-shot for tool call patterns.

## 9.3 Embeddings

* Local `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` or OpenRouter embeddings if free; embeddings precompute for all meds and synonyms.

